1
00:01:23,049 --> 00:01:26,541
<i>[Man On Radio] Ghost Two,</i>
<i>this is Echo One. Ghost Two, this is Echo One.</i>

2
00:01:26,653 --> 00:01:29,622
<i>E.T.A.: four minutes.</i>
<i>Repeat: four minutes.</i>

3
00:01:37,297 --> 00:01:41,131
- [Both Grunting]
- <i>[Man Shouting In Foreign Language]</i>

4
00:01:43,803 --> 00:01:46,704
[Continues In Foreign Language]

5
00:01:56,583 --> 00:01:58,483
Intel confirmed.
Nine hostiles, three marines.

6
00:01:58,585 --> 00:02:01,486
<i>[Man On Radio] Ghost Two, you are not</i>
<i>to engage. Alpha Team is on its way.</i>

7
00:02:01,588 --> 00:02:04,386
No time.

8
00:02:08,761 --> 00:02:11,161
[Shouting In Foreign Language]

9
00:02:18,304 --> 00:02:20,295
[Yelling]

10
00:02:55,307 --> 00:02:57,537
- You guys ready to go home?
- Yeah.

11
00:03:18,864 --> 00:03:21,560
- How do we get around 'em?
- We don't.

12
00:03:24,737 --> 00:03:27,399
We go through 'em.

13
00:03:31,009 --> 00:03:33,739
<i>[Soldiers Shouting In Distance]</i>

14
00:03:38,416 --> 00:03:41,078
<i>[Man]</i>
<i>Atten-hut! Look sharp, marine.</i>

15
00:03:41,185 --> 00:03:44,484
As you were, gentlemen.

16
00:03:44,588 --> 00:03:48,490
- Triton.
- Sir?

17
00:03:48,592 --> 00:03:51,322
Outside. Ten minutes.

18
00:03:51,429 --> 00:03:53,920
Yes, sir.

19
00:04:01,872 --> 00:04:05,069
<i>[Man] We've approached</i>
<i>this thing from every angle.</i>

20
00:04:05,176 --> 00:04:08,407
The judge advocate's done
hearing your case.

21
00:04:08,512 --> 00:04:11,948
- What about an appeal?
- They're not accepting more appeals.

22
00:04:13,384 --> 00:04:18,151
Bottom line is, you disobeyed a direct order.

23
00:04:18,255 --> 00:04:20,314
You're being discharged.

24
00:04:24,228 --> 00:04:27,789
You served your unit, your corps
and your country with honor, son.

25
00:04:27,898 --> 00:04:30,867
Walk away with dignity.

26
00:04:33,137 --> 00:04:35,731
Colonel...

27
00:04:35,840 --> 00:04:37,967
I'm a marine.

28
00:04:39,477 --> 00:04:43,174
One of the best. Remember that.

29
00:04:43,280 --> 00:04:48,149
On behalf of a grateful nation
and the United States Marine Corps...

30
00:04:48,252 --> 00:04:51,517
I thank you for your loyal service.

31
00:05:43,374 --> 00:05:46,207
- Thank you.
- Oh!

32
00:05:54,852 --> 00:05:56,752
You're home.

33
00:06:22,346 --> 00:06:24,746
- You all right?
- Yeah.

34
00:06:24,848 --> 00:06:29,444
Yeah, I just- I can't believe you're here.

35
00:06:42,533 --> 00:06:45,900
You know, the hardest thing...

36
00:06:46,003 --> 00:06:49,461
about you leaving was not knowing.

37
00:06:50,874 --> 00:06:55,106
You know, not knowing
where you were...

38
00:06:55,212 --> 00:06:57,840
not knowing if you're coming home...

39
00:06:57,948 --> 00:07:02,681
not knowing if I'm gonna get
that phone call saying that you wouldn't be.

40
00:07:02,786 --> 00:07:05,584
You married a marine, Kate.

41
00:07:05,689 --> 00:07:09,181
I know it's not gonna be
easy for you, John.

42
00:07:09,293 --> 00:07:11,727
We'll figure it out together.

43
00:07:13,764 --> 00:07:17,063
I'm home now, and I'm not goin' anywhere.

44
00:07:17,167 --> 00:07:22,104
Good. And speaking of that...

45
00:07:22,206 --> 00:07:24,106
are you sure about
starting this job tomorrow?

46
00:07:24,208 --> 00:07:28,042
- Oh!
- I just think there's so many
other things you could be doing.

47
00:07:28,145 --> 00:07:31,114
If I sat around here all day, I'd go insane.

48
00:07:32,816 --> 00:07:36,343
I just want you to be happy, John.

49
00:07:36,453 --> 00:07:39,013
I am happy. Come on.

50
00:07:39,123 --> 00:07:42,889
- Oh! Geez. Where are we going?
- To make me happy.

51
00:07:56,407 --> 00:07:59,535
- I'll be right back.
- [Cuban Accent] You got it, man.

52
00:07:59,643 --> 00:08:01,543
What?

53
00:08:01,645 --> 00:08:04,876
You got it, man.
You know, <i>Scarface</i>. Come on.

54
00:08:04,982 --> 00:08:07,348
Do it again.

55
00:08:07,451 --> 00:08:09,385
Okay. You got it, man.

56
00:08:09,486 --> 00:08:12,216
Wow. That's horrible.

57
00:08:52,730 --> 00:08:55,062
[No Audible Dialogue]

58
00:09:16,053 --> 00:09:17,884
- How you doing?
- Fine, sir.

59
00:09:36,940 --> 00:09:39,067
Excuse me.

60
00:09:39,176 --> 00:09:41,508
<i>[Customers Screaming, Gasping]</i>

61
00:09:44,214 --> 00:09:46,341
Everybody down.

62
00:09:47,918 --> 00:09:50,944
Everybody on the ground, now!

63
00:09:53,390 --> 00:09:55,950
Ladies and gentlemen,
keep your heads down and your mouths shut.

64
00:09:56,059 --> 00:09:58,823
I don't wanna see any eye contact.

65
00:09:58,929 --> 00:10:01,523
<i>I have severe intimacy issues and a gun...</i>

66
00:10:01,632 --> 00:10:04,533
so do yourselves a favor
and don't look up.

67
00:10:08,572 --> 00:10:10,631
What I want is on
the other side of this door...

68
00:10:10,741 --> 00:10:16,179
but that's gonna be a little tricky
because... it's bulletproof.

69
00:10:16,280 --> 00:10:19,772
So here's how we're gonna do it.
Hi, honey. Can I borrow you for a second?

70
00:10:19,883 --> 00:10:21,544
[Screaming]

71
00:10:21,652 --> 00:10:24,644
- How you doin' in there, sport?
- <i>[Woman] Oh, God! Please!</i>

72
00:10:24,755 --> 00:10:28,486
Oh, don't look at him.
He can't help you.

73
00:10:28,592 --> 00:10:30,685
Please! I have children!

74
00:10:30,794 --> 00:10:33,490
I don't think he cares.

75
00:10:33,597 --> 00:10:36,725
Please!
[Screams]

76
00:10:36,834 --> 00:10:39,803
[Beeping]

77
00:10:54,184 --> 00:10:56,982
Fill it.

78
00:11:04,027 --> 00:11:06,996
Get down!

79
00:11:21,345 --> 00:11:24,781
Thank you.

80
00:11:24,882 --> 00:11:27,715
Rome.

81
00:11:29,052 --> 00:11:32,044
<i>You gotta hit me.</i>
<i>It's gotta look real-</i>

82
00:11:32,155 --> 00:11:34,180
For the cops.

83
00:11:43,163 --> 00:11:45,063
That's real.

84
00:11:48,535 --> 00:11:50,503
Well, the cops are comin'.

85
00:11:50,604 --> 00:11:53,971
I'd love to stay and chat,
but, uh, I can't.

86
00:11:54,074 --> 00:11:58,033
I apologize for that little
outburst of anger I showed earlier.

87
00:11:58,144 --> 00:12:00,510
That's really more for dramatic purposes
than anything else.

88
00:12:00,614 --> 00:12:04,448
I hope that what I've done here today
doesn't force you to have...

89
00:12:04,551 --> 00:12:09,545
a negative opinion of me or how you think
I feel about the great state of South Carolina.

90
00:12:09,656 --> 00:12:12,090
'Cause I love it here. I do.

91
00:12:12,192 --> 00:12:14,922
I love the people.

92
00:12:15,028 --> 00:12:17,724
Enjoy the rest of your day.

93
00:12:29,142 --> 00:12:33,238
<i>[Sirens Wailing In Distance]</i>

94
00:13:14,154 --> 00:13:16,054
What? Too much?

95
00:13:17,490 --> 00:13:19,617
[Tires Screeching]

96
00:13:25,498 --> 00:13:27,466
Ooh!

97
00:13:39,746 --> 00:13:43,113
Okay.

98
00:13:43,216 --> 00:13:45,741
We know how they got in here.

99
00:13:45,852 --> 00:13:48,719
Once they're in, they don't bother
with any small stuff.

100
00:13:48,822 --> 00:13:53,225
They just go right for the vault
with 12 million in diamonds in it.

101
00:13:53,326 --> 00:13:56,523
The same diamonds
that were delivered just 24 hours ago.

102
00:13:56,629 --> 00:13:59,826
What are the odds of that?

103
00:13:59,933 --> 00:14:02,231
And how did our guys know...

104
00:14:02,335 --> 00:14:04,701
that they were gonna get
so lucky today?

105
00:14:04,804 --> 00:14:07,705
We could ask our friend
on the floor over there.

106
00:14:07,807 --> 00:14:10,071
I'll bet he knows.

107
00:14:15,515 --> 00:14:17,574
[Chattering]

108
00:14:25,325 --> 00:14:27,259
I don't care.

109
00:14:27,360 --> 00:14:30,227
No, do you understand
what I'm saying? Oh, really?

110
00:14:30,330 --> 00:14:33,458
See if you can understand this.

111
00:14:45,678 --> 00:14:48,044
[Chuckling]

112
00:14:52,352 --> 00:14:55,116
Is this what you do all day?

113
00:14:55,221 --> 00:14:57,815
Hmm? I had a Game Boy...

114
00:14:57,924 --> 00:14:59,824
but they took it.

115
00:15:08,034 --> 00:15:11,595
Come on, man. This is a great job.

116
00:15:11,704 --> 00:15:14,673
Good benefits. Great money.

117
00:15:14,774 --> 00:15:17,766
<i>A couple two, three years,</i>
<i>they move you to management.</i>

118
00:15:19,212 --> 00:15:21,112
How long you been working here?

119
00:15:21,214 --> 00:15:23,114
Nine years.

120
00:15:24,451 --> 00:15:26,351
How come you're not in management?

121
00:15:28,421 --> 00:15:31,948
<i>[Phone Ringing]</i>

122
00:15:32,058 --> 00:15:33,650
Security.

123
00:15:35,528 --> 00:15:39,658
We'll be right there.
Psycho ex-boyfriend on 12.

124
00:15:42,602 --> 00:15:45,867
Rick, have you lost your mind?
This is my job.

125
00:15:45,972 --> 00:15:48,634
Oh, really? It doesn't
look like a whorehouse.

126
00:15:48,741 --> 00:15:51,141
Where's all the other whores?
Where's your pimp?

127
00:15:51,244 --> 00:15:55,010
<i>You were with him. That's the reason you</i>
<i>didn't answer your cellphone all weekend!</i>

128
00:15:55,114 --> 00:15:57,275
Sir, could you please come with us?

129
00:15:57,383 --> 00:15:59,442
Don't mess with me, pork chop.

130
00:15:59,552 --> 00:16:01,679
- "Pork chop"?
- <i>You're causing a scene.</i>

131
00:16:01,788 --> 00:16:05,952
You think this is a scene? Wait till I tell
Daddy about the little whore he raised!

132
00:16:06,059 --> 00:16:09,222
- Sir, I'm just gonna have to ask you-
- Ask me to what?

133
00:16:09,329 --> 00:16:13,993
- Take a seat, flattop. I'll get to you in a second.
- Oh, really?

134
00:16:14,100 --> 00:16:18,696
Get your hands off me!
Why are you so angry?

135
00:16:22,008 --> 00:16:24,238
<i>[Cellphone Ringing]</i>

136
00:16:24,344 --> 00:16:28,337
You got the Drake.
Dude, let me call you back later.

137
00:16:28,448 --> 00:16:30,575
Because I am trapped in an elevator...

138
00:16:30,683 --> 00:16:32,708
- with a couple of jackasses, that's why!
- <i>[Elevator Bell Dings]</i>

139
00:16:39,359 --> 00:16:42,487
We kindly ask you
to leave the premises, sir.

140
00:16:43,830 --> 00:16:46,230
Thanks.

141
00:16:49,969 --> 00:16:54,338
Seriously, just spit-balling here.
Tell me if I'm close.

142
00:16:54,440 --> 00:16:57,841
Right out of high school,
straight into the military?

143
00:16:57,944 --> 00:17:00,777
Realized you'd never be
all you thought you could be...

144
00:17:00,880 --> 00:17:03,906
and that's how you ended up
as a rent-a-cop.

145
00:17:04,017 --> 00:17:07,009
Tell me I'm wrong.

146
00:17:08,521 --> 00:17:11,081
Whoa! Whoa, whoa, whoa.
Hey, wait a minute. Wait a minute.

147
00:17:11,190 --> 00:17:14,182
- The genie tried to hit me!
- I know. I saw that,
and he shouldn't have done that.

148
00:17:14,294 --> 00:17:17,457
You shouldn't have done that.
But he missed, and you're fine.

149
00:17:17,564 --> 00:17:20,863
<i>We deal with people like this every day,</i>
<i>and in order to avoid an incident...</i>

150
00:17:20,967 --> 00:17:22,867
sometimes you just
gotta let things go.

151
00:17:22,969 --> 00:17:26,871
<i>Yeah? Well, you better</i>
<i>tell your boyfriend to back off.</i>

152
00:17:26,973 --> 00:17:31,069
Unfortunately for the genie,
this is not one of those times.

153
00:17:50,196 --> 00:17:52,460
Oh!

154
00:17:52,565 --> 00:17:54,965
[Gasping]

155
00:17:56,569 --> 00:18:00,437
It's on now. See, you really messed up.

156
00:18:00,540 --> 00:18:03,236
Somewhere, somehow,
somebody just got all this on video.

157
00:18:05,044 --> 00:18:08,309
<i>By the time you go to sleep tonight,</i>
<i>I'm gonna own this building.</i>

158
00:18:08,414 --> 00:18:11,406
And tomorrow...

159
00:18:11,517 --> 00:18:14,008
don't be late.

160
00:18:14,120 --> 00:18:18,147
'Cause when you clock in, you're fired!

161
00:18:36,109 --> 00:18:38,009
Johnny.

162
00:18:42,815 --> 00:18:44,806
[Clears Throat]
A toast.

163
00:18:44,917 --> 00:18:48,011
To your first and last day on the job.

164
00:18:48,121 --> 00:18:50,919
[Chuckles]
Yeah.

165
00:18:51,024 --> 00:18:53,356
- About that-
- Dude, I told you, don't worry about it.

166
00:18:53,459 --> 00:18:55,950
It's not the first time
I've been suspended.

167
00:18:56,062 --> 00:18:59,293
That's not it. Um-

168
00:18:59,399 --> 00:19:02,334
You'll find another job.
You got all that training.

169
00:19:02,435 --> 00:19:04,835
Training.

170
00:19:04,937 --> 00:19:08,532
Covert reconnaissance.
Close-quarter hand-to-hand combat.

171
00:19:08,641 --> 00:19:10,541
Demolition.

172
00:19:10,643 --> 00:19:13,043
Not a high call in the workplace
for skills like that, Joe.

173
00:19:13,146 --> 00:19:16,809
Okay, but you're a smart guy.
You can do whatever you want.

174
00:19:16,916 --> 00:19:19,476
You don't get it. It's not-

175
00:19:19,585 --> 00:19:22,713
It's not about work.
It's not about a job.

176
00:19:22,822 --> 00:19:24,847
Being a marine meant everything to me.

177
00:19:27,960 --> 00:19:32,260
Now I go and get fired
from some bullshit security job.

178
00:19:32,365 --> 00:19:35,391
Sorry.

179
00:19:35,501 --> 00:19:37,696
I don't know what to do.

180
00:19:39,906 --> 00:19:42,204
Look.

181
00:19:42,308 --> 00:19:46,574
I'm not gonna try and pretend
I know what you're going through...

182
00:19:46,679 --> 00:19:48,647
'cause I don't.

183
00:19:50,450 --> 00:19:54,682
And-And your time as a marine-
Yeah, it's over.

184
00:19:54,787 --> 00:19:57,915
And that sucks, man.

185
00:19:58,024 --> 00:19:59,924
But your life's not over.

186
00:20:00,026 --> 00:20:02,551
<i>I mean, it's changing...</i>

187
00:20:02,662 --> 00:20:04,630
but you gotta learn to change with it.

188
00:20:07,266 --> 00:20:09,496
Sometimes-

189
00:20:09,602 --> 00:20:14,301
Sometimes, it's good to just take
a step back and see what you still have.

190
00:20:19,011 --> 00:20:22,742
You know, I think I'm gonna
go home and see my wife.

191
00:20:22,849 --> 00:20:25,044
Yeah. She's hot.

192
00:20:36,162 --> 00:20:38,596
What happened today?

193
00:20:44,170 --> 00:20:47,662
We made a lot of money.

194
00:20:47,774 --> 00:20:50,470
In the vault... with the kid.

195
00:20:52,111 --> 00:20:54,602
That kid showed that
he couldn't keep his mouth shut.

196
00:20:54,714 --> 00:20:58,980
And Morgan blowin' up that cop car?

197
00:20:59,085 --> 00:21:01,315
He went a little overboard.

198
00:21:01,420 --> 00:21:03,786
But in all fairness to Morgan...

199
00:21:03,890 --> 00:21:07,553
I was firing an automatic weapon at those cops.

200
00:21:07,660 --> 00:21:11,152
Dead cops, all those witnesses-

201
00:21:11,264 --> 00:21:13,755
Doesn't that pose
a potential problem for us?

202
00:21:13,866 --> 00:21:17,063
So does a prison term.

203
00:21:17,170 --> 00:21:20,731
Bottom line is, we got away clean.

204
00:21:24,610 --> 00:21:26,942
What's the matter, Angela?

205
00:21:27,046 --> 00:21:29,571
Don't you trust me anymore?

206
00:21:36,622 --> 00:21:38,590
Look at me.

207
00:21:41,394 --> 00:21:43,862
That kid knew my name.

208
00:21:43,963 --> 00:21:47,865
That's dangerous for all of us.

209
00:21:47,967 --> 00:21:51,994
Baby, is there anything in these eyes that
makes you think I could ever hurt you?

210
00:21:57,777 --> 00:21:59,802
<i>[Cellphone Ringing]</i>

211
00:22:04,817 --> 00:22:08,753
- What?
- [Man] Let's forget about what
you did to our guy in the vault.

212
00:22:08,855 --> 00:22:12,985
You killed two cops today,
and that's a problem.

213
00:22:13,092 --> 00:22:14,992
Don't start with me.

214
00:22:15,094 --> 00:22:17,494
You arrogant bastard.
You've lost control.

215
00:22:17,597 --> 00:22:19,929
That's where you're wrong, my friend.

216
00:22:20,032 --> 00:22:22,330
You see...

217
00:22:24,971 --> 00:22:28,202
- I've gained control.
- Is that right?

218
00:22:28,307 --> 00:22:30,775
You bet your ass that's right.

219
00:22:30,877 --> 00:22:33,869
<i>What's the matter with you, Rome?</i>
<i>Have you lost your mind?</i>

220
00:22:33,980 --> 00:22:36,175
<i>Have you forgotten</i>
<i>who you're talking to?</i>

221
00:22:36,282 --> 00:22:39,149
I know exactly who I'm talking to.

222
00:22:39,252 --> 00:22:42,619
You see, I have the diamonds.
Therefore, I have the power.

223
00:22:42,722 --> 00:22:46,021
You have no idea of the level of hell
I could bring down on you.

224
00:22:46,125 --> 00:22:49,652
Yeah, but you won't,
not if you wanna see these diamonds.

225
00:22:49,762 --> 00:22:53,698
Tomorrow, noon. I get my diamonds,
you get your money.

226
00:22:53,799 --> 00:22:56,233
<i>[Thunder Rumbling]</i>

227
00:22:56,335 --> 00:22:58,200
[Beeps Off]

228
00:23:08,414 --> 00:23:13,147
Listen. About what happened at work today-

229
00:23:13,252 --> 00:23:16,085
I'm not tellin' anybody.

230
00:23:16,188 --> 00:23:18,156
Cool.

231
00:23:31,203 --> 00:23:33,728
- Hey, baby.
- Hey.

232
00:23:33,839 --> 00:23:36,569
- How was work?
- Fine.

233
00:23:36,676 --> 00:23:40,442
Yeah? What? What happened?

234
00:23:40,546 --> 00:23:43,777
- Talk to me.
- Nothing.

235
00:23:44,884 --> 00:23:46,647
Stuff.

236
00:23:46,752 --> 00:23:49,016
<i>[Man On TV]</i>
<i>They're hired to protect us.</i>

237
00:23:49,121 --> 00:23:51,749
But who will protect us from them?

238
00:23:51,857 --> 00:23:55,588
- Security guards out of control tonight at 11:00.
- Mmm.

239
00:23:55,695 --> 00:23:59,290
"Stuff." Like you throwing
a guy out of a window?

240
00:23:59,398 --> 00:24:01,992
Yeah.

241
00:24:03,235 --> 00:24:05,203
<i>[TV Shuts Off]</i>

242
00:24:05,304 --> 00:24:09,035
I thought my days of worrying
about you were over.

243
00:24:09,141 --> 00:24:12,577
- What happened?
