331
00:31:31,884 --> 00:31:33,749
Couple times a year.

332
00:31:33,852 --> 00:31:36,184
Me too. My mom lives there.

333
00:31:36,288 --> 00:31:38,518
I just love it there, you know?

334
00:31:38,624 --> 00:31:40,956
Especially downtown.

335
00:31:42,161 --> 00:31:44,220
<i>You ever go to the Olympus?</i>

336
00:31:44,329 --> 00:31:46,889
Oh, not since they tore it down last year.

337
00:31:48,634 --> 00:31:50,226
Oh, man.

338
00:31:50,261 --> 00:31:50,419
Oh, man.

339
00:31:50,526 --> 00:31:52,756
[Gasps]

340
00:31:52,861 --> 00:31:55,591
- Don't move.
- [Tires Screeching]

341
00:32:21,489 --> 00:32:23,389
Great.

342
00:32:25,493 --> 00:32:27,791
Take the truck!

343
00:32:29,664 --> 00:32:32,064
[Screaming]

344
00:32:34,168 --> 00:32:37,137
Come here! Where you goin'? Come here!

345
00:32:37,238 --> 00:32:41,231
- Stay down!
- John!

346
00:32:42,543 --> 00:32:45,569
- Shut up!
- John!

347
00:32:45,680 --> 00:32:50,083
- Get off of me! John!
- Where the hell did she come from?

348
00:32:50,184 --> 00:32:54,314
- Do we kill her?
- No. We might need a hostage.

349
00:32:54,422 --> 00:32:57,084
<i>[Kate's Voice, Distorted]</i>
<i>John!</i>

350
00:32:59,760 --> 00:33:03,856
<i>Get off me! John!</i>

351
00:33:15,076 --> 00:33:17,340
<i>Morgan, get in the truck!</i>

352
00:34:36,857 --> 00:34:40,384
Okay, keep pressure on that.
I'm gonna call for help.

353
00:35:01,749 --> 00:35:04,149
Highway Patrol, this is John Triton.

354
00:35:04,251 --> 00:35:07,778
You have officers down at Manze's Gas.
Multiple assailants.

355
00:35:07,888 --> 00:35:11,449
Four men, one woman headed
southbound on I-95 in a black Navigator.

356
00:35:11,559 --> 00:35:14,323
They have a hostage. It's my wife.

357
00:35:39,019 --> 00:35:42,182
"Kate Triton." Married to John Triton.

358
00:35:42,289 --> 00:35:44,587
<i>Sergeant John Triton.</i>

359
00:35:44,692 --> 00:35:46,626
She married a marine.

360
00:35:46,727 --> 00:35:50,288
What'd you marry him for? Benefits?

361
00:35:50,397 --> 00:35:52,297
[Chuckling]

362
00:35:52,399 --> 00:35:54,299
Hey!

363
00:35:54,401 --> 00:35:56,665
- Settle down!
- Get off me!

364
00:35:56,770 --> 00:36:00,001
<i>Settle down!</i>

365
00:36:04,578 --> 00:36:06,478
You gotta be kiddin' me.

366
00:36:08,816 --> 00:36:10,511
The cops.

367
00:36:10,618 --> 00:36:13,781
That ain't the cops.

368
00:36:15,489 --> 00:36:18,219
I hate cops.

369
00:36:18,325 --> 00:36:20,350
And rock candy.

370
00:36:23,964 --> 00:36:26,330
- Shoot him.
- [Screams]

371
00:37:25,226 --> 00:37:26,955
Will somebody please shoot this guy!

372
00:37:27,061 --> 00:37:29,552
- What does it look like we're doing?
- Missing.

373
00:37:46,647 --> 00:37:48,945
Hey, slow down!

374
00:37:53,487 --> 00:37:55,614
Look out!

375
00:37:59,059 --> 00:38:01,653
Hey!

376
00:38:11,772 --> 00:38:14,172
Whoa!

377
00:38:52,780 --> 00:38:55,112
No, no, no, no!

378
00:39:07,061 --> 00:39:10,292
This guy's like the Terminator.

379
00:40:23,737 --> 00:40:26,729
You murdering sons of bitches!

380
00:40:26,840 --> 00:40:28,865
Somebody shut her up
and get her out of here.

381
00:40:28,976 --> 00:40:31,877
<i>You murderers!</i>
<i>[Yelling]</i>

382
00:40:33,981 --> 00:40:37,041
Angie, baby, I know
you got a hair trigger...

383
00:40:37,151 --> 00:40:39,142
<i>but I said shut her up, not kill her.</i>

384
00:40:39,253 --> 00:40:41,983
We might need an insurance policy.

385
00:40:43,724 --> 00:40:46,124
Get a rope and tie her up.

386
00:40:57,838 --> 00:41:00,432
Put your hands together.

387
00:41:02,342 --> 00:41:05,004
Front axle's history.

388
00:41:05,112 --> 00:41:07,512
We're not goin' anywhere in this thing.

389
00:41:07,614 --> 00:41:11,607
- Now, you figured that out all by yourself, huh?
- Actually, I did.

390
00:41:11,718 --> 00:41:15,620
Yeah. But, hey,
you know what else I figured out?

391
00:41:15,722 --> 00:41:17,883
What's that?

392
00:41:17,991 --> 00:41:21,427
That you're a trigger-happy nut job
who belongs in a cage.

393
00:41:25,065 --> 00:41:27,499
[Fires Gun Twice]

394
00:41:27,601 --> 00:41:31,037
All right!
We are monumentally screwed here...

395
00:41:31,138 --> 00:41:34,596
and the last thing I need is you two
bickerin' like a couple of little girls.

396
00:41:34,708 --> 00:41:37,768
<i>So as of right now, it's over.</i>
<i>Are we clear?</i>

397
00:41:37,878 --> 00:41:41,370
<i>Because if we're not,</i>
<i>I give you my word...</i>

398
00:41:41,482 --> 00:41:43,507
I will absolutely shoot you myself.

399
00:41:43,617 --> 00:41:47,986
- What do we do now?
- The way I see it, we got two options.

400
00:41:48,088 --> 00:41:51,455
"A," we stand here
and try to kill each other-

401
00:41:51,558 --> 00:41:54,652
and then no one gets paid
and someone gets dead-

402
00:41:54,761 --> 00:41:58,527
<i>or "B," we get out of the swamp,</i>
<i>make our drop and collect our dough.</i>

403
00:41:58,632 --> 00:42:01,897
And maybe it's just the greed talkin',
but I'm stickin' with "B."

404
00:42:02,002 --> 00:42:05,836
Yeah, well, I say we move, 'cause
every cop in the state heard that blast.

405
00:42:05,939 --> 00:42:08,305
We'll follow the swamp downstream.

406
00:42:08,408 --> 00:42:11,070
- Through there?
- Yeah, through there.

407
00:42:11,178 --> 00:42:14,978
<i>The trees'll give us</i>
<i>cover from the air.</i>

408
00:42:15,082 --> 00:42:17,550
The swamp will slow down the cops.

409
00:42:17,651 --> 00:42:19,846
What do you wanna do
with our little insurance policy?

410
00:42:19,953 --> 00:42:23,218
Oh, go to hell.

411
00:42:23,323 --> 00:42:26,087
Angie, why'd you do that?

412
00:42:26,193 --> 00:42:29,822
<i>Now Morgan's gotta carry her.</i>

413
00:42:29,930 --> 00:42:33,093
Morgan's got-
Morgan's gotta do what?

414
00:42:43,043 --> 00:42:45,102
Watch out for crocodiles.

415
00:42:45,212 --> 00:42:48,340
What's the matter with you?
Ain't no crocodiles in South Carolina.

416
00:42:48,549 --> 00:42:50,449
[Siren Chirping]

417
00:43:07,367 --> 00:43:09,426
- Detective Van Buren.
- Sir.

418
00:43:09,536 --> 00:43:14,132
- What do we got?
- Well, we got one deceased officer here...

419
00:43:14,241 --> 00:43:18,405
and another found
seriously wounded there.

420
00:43:18,512 --> 00:43:21,242
The guy who called in?

421
00:43:21,348 --> 00:43:25,409
John Triton. He's an ex-marine,
and he's for real.

422
00:43:25,519 --> 00:43:27,987
His description of the perps
sounds like the crew...

423
00:43:28,088 --> 00:43:30,784
that hit the diamond store
in town yesterday.

424
00:43:30,891 --> 00:43:34,054
- Roadblocks up?
- Yes, sir.

425
00:43:34,161 --> 00:43:36,652
Choppers and search teams
are on their way.

426
00:43:36,763 --> 00:43:41,723
- So what else do we know about these guys?
- They're sloppy.

427
00:43:41,835 --> 00:43:44,326
<i>[Man On Radio]</i>
<i>Unit four, come in.</i>

428
00:43:46,873 --> 00:43:49,774
- Go ahead.
- We got a report of a multiple car accident.

429
00:43:49,876 --> 00:43:52,140
Shots fired five miles
south of your position.

430
00:43:52,245 --> 00:43:55,840
That Highway Patrol car from your location
was involved. Check and advise.

431
00:43:55,949 --> 00:43:57,644
I'm en route.

432
00:44:21,708 --> 00:44:24,142
<i>[Branches Rustling]</i>

433
00:44:26,046 --> 00:44:29,743
Detective Van Buren, Homicide.

434
00:44:29,850 --> 00:44:32,045
I'm gonna assume you're John Triton.

435
00:44:36,990 --> 00:44:41,188
- They took my wife.
- That's a matter for law enforcement now.

436
00:44:41,294 --> 00:44:44,855
Listen, I've seen 'em kill three people.

437
00:44:44,965 --> 00:44:47,229
<i>My wife will not be number four.</i>

438
00:44:47,334 --> 00:44:51,498
- I can't give you permission to pursue.
- I'm not asking for it.

439
00:44:51,605 --> 00:44:55,041
You know, this whole area's tidal.

440
00:44:55,142 --> 00:44:58,703
The way the water level changes,
these guys are gonna be impossible to track.

441
00:44:58,812 --> 00:45:02,304
- I can handle it.
- <i>Triton?</i>

442
00:45:02,416 --> 00:45:04,577
I've seen what these guys can do.

443
00:45:06,119 --> 00:45:08,417
You better hurry.

444
00:45:10,424 --> 00:45:15,384
Get the chains out. I want
this river dragged. Are we in the air yet?

445
00:45:56,803 --> 00:45:59,237
[Grunting]

446
00:46:02,976 --> 00:46:04,876
[Grunts]

447
00:46:09,516 --> 00:46:12,815
If you and I are gonna be friends,
you need to learn some manners.

448
00:46:12,919 --> 00:46:14,944
- [Groans]
- Bitch.

449
00:46:15,055 --> 00:46:18,547
[Grunts]
Man, the hell with this.

450
00:46:18,658 --> 00:46:21,252
What, do you got a problem, brother?

451
00:46:21,361 --> 00:46:25,627
