462
00:46:57,931 --> 00:47:00,161
The black man.

463
00:47:01,768 --> 00:47:04,828
That's right, Vescera.
The black man.

464
00:47:04,938 --> 00:47:09,602
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.
Morgan, you are one crazy son of a bitch.

465
00:47:10,644 --> 00:47:13,135
I like that. I do.

466
00:47:13,246 --> 00:47:16,682
<i>But no one's gonna get killed here</i>
<i>until I give the go-ahead...</i>

467
00:47:16,783 --> 00:47:19,513
and I didn't give it.

468
00:47:22,088 --> 00:47:24,283
[Screams]

469
00:47:26,126 --> 00:47:28,390
<i>[Whimpering]</i>

470
00:47:28,495 --> 00:47:31,623
- What was that?
- The go-ahead.

471
00:47:38,004 --> 00:47:39,904
<i>[Angela]</i>
<i>Why Vescera?</i>

472
00:47:40,006 --> 00:47:42,839
You never know when
you'll need a crazy son of a bitch.

473
00:47:44,678 --> 00:47:46,578
<i>[Growling]</i>

474
00:47:48,348 --> 00:47:52,011
- I thought you said there were no crocodiles.
- Those are alligators.

475
00:47:52,118 --> 00:47:53,915
[Growls, Snarls]

476
00:47:54,020 --> 00:47:56,420
Do you think they're hungry?

477
00:47:56,523 --> 00:47:58,491
Not anymore.

478
00:48:02,195 --> 00:48:05,392
[Growling, Snarling]

479
00:48:05,565 --> 00:48:09,160
- What do you got?
- Nothin' yet.

480
00:48:12,772 --> 00:48:15,673
There's no way anybody
could have lived through this.

481
00:48:15,775 --> 00:48:19,506
- Keep me informed.
- Yes, sir.

482
00:48:45,805 --> 00:48:48,706
<i>[Dogs Barking]</i>

483
00:48:52,913 --> 00:48:55,905
[Panting]

484
00:49:50,270 --> 00:49:52,329
<i>[Cellphone Ringing]</i>

485
00:49:54,441 --> 00:49:56,500
- [Ringing]
- Yeah?

486
00:49:56,609 --> 00:49:59,203
- [Man] Where are you?
- How ya doin'?

487
00:49:59,312 --> 00:50:01,678
- How am I doing?
- Not so good, huh?

488
00:50:01,781 --> 00:50:04,682
Well, you know that triple homicide
I was just involved in?

489
00:50:04,784 --> 00:50:08,242
- The one all over the news?
- Yeah, right. That's the one. Yeah, I know. Bad.

490
00:50:08,355 --> 00:50:12,792
Anyways, I think I can now add
kidnapping to my litany of atrocities.

491
00:50:12,892 --> 00:50:16,726
As a matter of fact, I know I can, because
she's standing there right in front of me.

492
00:50:16,830 --> 00:50:19,731
- <i>Why are you telling me all this?</i>
- Why am I telling you all this?

493
00:50:19,833 --> 00:50:22,028
Well, because in the middle
of blowing up the gas station...

494
00:50:22,135 --> 00:50:26,071
killing the marine and now kidnapping,
I had a great idea-

495
00:50:26,172 --> 00:50:28,333
As a matter of fact,
it's such a great idea...

496
00:50:28,441 --> 00:50:30,534
that I even came up
with a name for it.

497
00:50:30,643 --> 00:50:32,873
It's called "you're out."

498
00:50:32,979 --> 00:50:36,540
<i>Which basically means</i>
<i>you get nothing-</i>

499
00:50:36,649 --> 00:50:40,210
No split, no diamonds,
no payoff, no nothing.

500
00:50:40,320 --> 00:50:44,222
- We had a plan, Rome.
- I know we had a plan, but plans change.

501
00:50:44,324 --> 00:50:47,020
At least, for one of us they do.

502
00:50:47,127 --> 00:50:49,322
Now listen, if you think
for one second-

503
00:50:49,429 --> 00:50:51,329
There's no way you can
get away with this without me.

504
00:50:51,431 --> 00:50:52,557
- Can you hold on?
- Yeah.

505
00:50:52,665 --> 00:50:54,565
- [Beeps]
- Yeah?

506
00:50:54,667 --> 00:50:56,464
- [Woman, Indistinct]
- This is he.

507
00:50:56,569 --> 00:50:58,332
I'm just calling to let you know...

508
00:50:58,438 --> 00:51:00,906
- that your order has been approved.
- Yeah?

509
00:51:01,007 --> 00:51:03,498
Now, does that include
all the premium channels...

510
00:51:03,610 --> 00:51:05,578
- and the sports package?
- It sure does.

511
00:51:10,717 --> 00:51:13,515
- [Groans]
- <i>[Helicopter Whirring]</i>

512
00:51:31,871 --> 00:51:34,635
All right, the air show's over.

513
00:51:34,741 --> 00:51:37,266
Let's get the hell out of here.

514
00:51:40,146 --> 00:51:42,114
Go on.

515
00:51:59,032 --> 00:52:01,626
<i>[Whirring]</i>

516
00:52:49,916 --> 00:52:54,444
That's a creepy-ass snake.
Slimy and scaly.

517
00:52:54,554 --> 00:52:57,523
It's terrifying, all these animals and bugs.

518
00:52:57,624 --> 00:53:01,025
I hate this, man.
I'm not built for this stuff.

519
00:53:01,127 --> 00:53:04,358
- What's wrong with you?
- What's wrong with me? Think about it.

520
00:53:04,464 --> 00:53:07,399
How many brothers
you see in <i>Deliverance</i>?

521
00:53:07,500 --> 00:53:09,400
The answer is "zero."

522
00:53:09,502 --> 00:53:12,369
Do you know why?
'Cause brothers don't camp.

523
00:53:12,472 --> 00:53:16,340
Why does everything always
have to be racial with you, Morgan?

524
00:53:16,442 --> 00:53:19,309
Why do you feel the need
to confine us to these labels?

525
00:53:19,412 --> 00:53:22,040
Why can't we just be people?

526
00:53:22,148 --> 00:53:24,173
What do you think, Kate?

527
00:53:24,284 --> 00:53:26,252
I think you're psychotic.

528
00:53:26,352 --> 00:53:29,913
Ho, ho. Now, how can you say that?

529
00:53:30,023 --> 00:53:32,389
You don't even know me.

530
00:53:32,492 --> 00:53:34,687
That's very judgmental.

531
00:53:38,631 --> 00:53:40,826
Is she looking at me?

532
00:53:46,973 --> 00:53:50,033
I'm gonna be totally honest here. I, uh-

533
00:53:50,143 --> 00:53:53,203
I thought that you and I, you know-

534
00:53:53,313 --> 00:53:56,441
We could have had a future,
you know, if it wasn't for-

535
00:54:00,119 --> 00:54:01,711
Mmm.

536
00:54:04,524 --> 00:54:07,789
- Mmm.
- What?

537
00:54:09,262 --> 00:54:12,288
- Mmm.
- You're insane.

538
00:54:16,135 --> 00:54:18,035
Maybe.

539
00:54:20,707 --> 00:54:22,698
[Whispering]
Good talk.

540
00:54:30,984 --> 00:54:33,350
- Cops.
- Get the truck loaded.

541
00:54:51,170 --> 00:54:53,900
<i>[Rustling]</i>

542
00:54:55,308 --> 00:54:57,833
<i>[Sharp Click]</i>

543
00:54:59,579 --> 00:55:02,343
- <i>[Grunts]</i>
- <i>[Clink]</i>

544
00:55:03,449 --> 00:55:05,815
Hold it right there, cop.

545
00:55:05,918 --> 00:55:08,478
[Sighs]

546
00:55:08,588 --> 00:55:11,148
I'm not a cop.

547
00:55:11,257 --> 00:55:13,521
I'm just looking for some people.

548
00:55:13,626 --> 00:55:15,526
Boy, I will end you.

549
00:55:18,464 --> 00:55:20,989
I told you, I'm not a cop.

550
00:55:28,808 --> 00:55:31,641
<i>[Muffled Yelling]</i>

551
00:55:31,744 --> 00:55:34,440
Wait here. And somebody shut her up.

552
00:55:40,753 --> 00:55:43,313
- What do you got?
- Nothin'.

553
00:55:43,423 --> 00:55:45,186
All right.

554
00:55:45,291 --> 00:55:47,191
- <i>[On Radio] Van Buren here.</i>
- <i>Sir, come in.</i>

555
00:55:47,293 --> 00:55:49,124
<i>What's goin' on at the south fork?</i>

556
00:55:49,228 --> 00:55:52,220
There's nothing here.
We're headed for the marina.

557
00:55:52,332 --> 00:55:55,358
I want every shack
on that riverbank searched.

558
00:55:55,468 --> 00:55:57,402
- Find 'em.
- Copy that.

559
00:56:01,941 --> 00:56:04,171
<i>[Engine Starts]</i>

560
00:56:11,617 --> 00:56:13,517
What did you find?

561
00:56:13,619 --> 00:56:16,918
There's a lodge up there.
It's swarmin' with cops.

562
00:56:18,024 --> 00:56:20,390
- [Muffled]
- What do you want to do now?

563
00:56:20,493 --> 00:56:24,020
We'll let the cops leave,
and then we'll cross the river.

564
00:56:30,103 --> 00:56:33,072
<i>[Rustling]</i>

565
00:56:37,777 --> 00:56:40,575
- <i>[Man, Indistinct]</i>
- <i>[Man #2] Get 'em loaded. We gotta move.</i>

566
00:56:44,016 --> 00:56:45,984
[Chains Clanking]

567
00:56:51,324 --> 00:56:54,452
What the hell you doin' out here, cop?

568
00:56:55,495 --> 00:56:57,429
You guys got it all wrong.

569
00:56:59,332 --> 00:57:02,062
Save your lies, boy.

570
00:57:04,070 --> 00:57:08,564
If I was a cop,
I'd have a badge. A gun.

571
00:57:08,674 --> 00:57:11,905
I don't. I'm just out here trying to-

572
00:57:17,517 --> 00:57:20,577
Just trying to what?

573
00:57:20,686 --> 00:57:22,620
They got choppers buzzin' around here.

574
00:57:22,722 --> 00:57:24,656
And I got you sneakin' up our asses.

575
00:57:24,757 --> 00:57:26,725
And you're not a cop?

576
00:57:29,762 --> 00:57:31,923
Right.

577
00:57:32,031 --> 00:57:33,931
You're right.

578
00:57:34,033 --> 00:57:35,933
I'm a cop.

579
00:57:36,035 --> 00:57:38,560
They're tracking
my G.P.S. right now.

580
00:57:38,671 --> 00:57:41,731
G.P.S.? I told you to search him.

581
00:57:41,841 --> 00:57:44,401
- I did!
- Find it!

582
00:57:44,510 --> 00:57:46,410
- <i>[Helicopter Whirring]</i>
- Where's the goddamn bug, cop?

583
00:57:58,257 --> 00:58:00,487
- [Growls]
- [Grunts]

584
00:58:05,364 --> 00:58:07,798
[Both Grunting, Groaning]

585
00:59:04,056 --> 00:59:06,991
<i>[Helicopter Whirring]</i>

586
00:59:12,665 --> 00:59:15,156
[Panting]

587
00:59:42,595 --> 00:59:44,529
<i>What you doin', man?</i>

588
00:59:44,630 --> 00:59:46,894
No contact point. No alarm.

589
00:59:46,999 --> 00:59:48,967
It's a freakin' shack.

590
00:59:52,505 --> 00:59:54,268
Get in there.

591
01:00:04,951 --> 01:00:06,919
Something die in here?

592
01:00:07,019 --> 01:00:10,147
I don't know, but it smells like baked ass.

593
01:00:12,258 --> 01:00:14,886
Morgan, see if you can
go find a generator.

594
01:00:16,562 --> 01:00:17,563
- Why me?
- Why not?

595
01:00:17,598 --> 01:00:19,224
- Why me?
- Why not?

596
01:00:19,332 --> 01:00:22,130
<i>What if there's some guy out there</i>
<i>with a hockey mask and a hatchet?</i>

597
01:00:22,234 --> 01:00:26,671
Or a group of country-ass crackers
cravin' some man love?

598
01:00:26,772 --> 01:00:28,933
It'll be fun, like summer camp.

599
01:00:29,041 --> 01:00:31,339
Yeah, but brothers don't camp.

600
01:00:32,478 --> 01:00:35,003
Well, actually, I did go to camp once.

601
01:00:35,114 --> 01:00:37,912
<i>I was 13 years old.</i>

602
01:00:39,986 --> 01:00:42,978
And there was this camp counselor-
Cool honky.

603
01:00:43,089 --> 01:00:45,523
Timothy.

604
01:00:45,625 --> 01:00:47,855
Tim.

605
01:00:49,095 --> 01:00:53,623
Or, as he liked to be called,
Johnny Whiplash.

606
01:00:56,502 --> 01:00:58,993
Well, tell us, Morgan,
what did this, uh...

607
01:00:59,105 --> 01:01:01,835
Johnny Whiplash have to offer?

608
01:01:03,609 --> 01:01:06,373
Well, at first, he offered friendship.

609
01:01:08,714 --> 01:01:11,706
Then some rock candy.

610
01:01:13,586 --> 01:01:18,148
Then he offered me something
that I never should have accepted.

611
01:01:19,258 --> 01:01:21,818
[Chuckles]

612
01:01:23,295 --> 01:01:25,661
Wow.

613
01:01:26,899 --> 01:01:28,958
Well, good luck with all that.

614
01:01:29,068 --> 01:01:32,299
Now go find the generator.

615
01:01:47,286 --> 01:01:49,186
Hey.

616
01:01:49,288 --> 01:01:51,848
Hey, what we talked about-

617
01:01:53,959 --> 01:01:56,655
<i>Ain't leavin' this room, right?</i>

618
01:01:56,762 --> 01:01:59,754
No. No.

619
01:01:59,865 --> 01:02:01,890
Now go find the goddamn generator.

620
01:02:59,618 --> 01:03:03,816
[Motor Turning Over, Sputtering]

621
01:03:09,861 --> 01:03:12,455
[Running Smoothly]

622
01:03:14,032 --> 01:03:16,694
## [Blues On Jukebox]

623
01:03:19,904 --> 01:03:21,963
Cool.

624
01:03:25,143 --> 01:03:27,077
<i>[Clanking]</i>

625
01:03:45,595 --> 01:03:49,258
[Both Grunting, Groaning]

626
01:04:11,254 --> 01:04:13,154
## <i>[Ends]</i>

627
01:04:29,571 --> 01:04:31,869
[Phone Beeping]

628
01:04:35,844 --> 01:04:38,836
[Ringing]

629
01:04:38,947 --> 01:04:41,313
- Hello.
- Yeah, hey. It's me.

630
01:04:41,416 --> 01:04:43,179
Hold on.

631
01:04:43,284 --> 01:04:45,013
- Frank.
- <i>What?</i>

632
01:04:45,119 --> 01:04:47,815
It's Rome.

633
01:04:51,793 --> 01:04:54,557
- So how's my Cadillac?
- Plan A's screwed.

634
01:04:54,662 --> 01:04:57,631
- No shit. You're all over the news.
- We're switching to plan "B."

635
01:04:57,732 --> 01:05:00,530
- [Laughs] What the hell is plan "B"?
- I don't know what plan "B" is.

636
01:05:00,635 --> 01:05:04,366
- <i>I'm makin' this up as I go.</i>
- Great.

637
01:05:04,472 --> 01:05:07,373
- You know that joint, Rita's, down by the marina?
- Yeah.

638
01:05:07,475 --> 01:05:10,171
- <i>I want you to leave a car there for me.</i>
- I'm gonna need time.

639
01:05:10,278 --> 01:05:13,111
- Give me till tomorrow.
- No. As soon as you can.

640
01:05:13,214 --> 01:05:16,411
<i>Looks like we're going to Phoenix.</i>

641
01:05:20,889 --> 01:05:23,187
What are you lookin' at?

642
01:05:38,106 --> 01:05:41,940
Why so sad?
Don't like your new friends?

643
01:05:42,043 --> 01:05:47,310
- You're pathetic.
- How so?

644
01:05:51,152 --> 01:05:54,451
- <i>[Door Closes]</i>
- You're like his little puppet.

645
01:06:04,232 --> 01:06:06,166
So what's the plan?

646
01:06:06,267 --> 01:06:08,292
Where are we goin'?

647
01:06:08,403 --> 01:06:10,803
What, no faith?

648
01:06:10,905 --> 01:06:11,906
I have faith. I just need to know
if I'm still in the loop.

649
01:06:11,941 --> 01:06:13,999
I have faith. I just need to know
if I'm still in the loop.

650
01:06:16,778 --> 01:06:19,212
There's this guy in Phoenix-

651
01:06:20,815 --> 01:06:23,147
I figure since we did 100% of the work...

652
01:06:23,251 --> 01:06:26,448
why not keep 100% of the diamonds?

653
01:06:27,588 --> 01:06:29,488
Can he move 'em?

654
01:06:29,590 --> 01:06:31,649
That he can, my friend.

655
01:06:31,759 --> 01:06:33,954
That he can.

656
01:06:37,432 --> 01:06:40,629
- You grew up on the water, right? Louisiana?
- Miami.

657
01:06:40,735 --> 01:06:42,999
Yeah, whatever.

658
01:06:43,104 --> 01:06:45,800
See if you can go get
that boat started out there.

659
01:06:48,109 --> 01:06:51,203
Hey, uh, Bennett.

660
01:06:52,380 --> 01:06:55,110
Check out Morgan.
See what he's up to.

661
01:07:15,903 --> 01:07:17,871
Morgan.

662
01:07:23,945 --> 01:07:26,209
[Groans]

663
01:07:33,021 --> 01:07:36,013
[Both Grunting, Groaning]

664
01:07:40,094 --> 01:07:41,994
<i>[Groans]</i>

665
01:08:01,616 --> 01:08:03,516
How many are left?

666
01:08:03,618 --> 01:08:05,677
There's two upstairs.

667
01:08:08,056 --> 01:08:10,217
- You wait here.
- I'm not waiting anywhere.

668
01:08:12,827 --> 01:08:14,795
You don't know what you're walking into.

669
01:08:14,896 --> 01:08:17,126
Listen. It's only a matter of time...

670
01:08:17,231 --> 01:08:19,222
before they realize
these two aren't coming back.

671
01:08:19,333 --> 01:08:22,234
I gotta do something,
and I gotta do it now.

672
01:08:24,472 --> 01:08:26,372
Okay.

673
01:08:29,243 --> 01:08:31,143
<i>[Sharp Click]</i>

674
01:08:31,245 --> 01:08:33,236
<i>[Generator Dies]</i>

675
01:08:43,825 --> 01:08:47,090
[Both Grunting, Groaning]

676
01:09:05,680 --> 01:09:07,341
Playtime's over.

677
01:09:09,517 --> 01:09:11,917
There's a crazy son of a bitch.

678
01:09:12,019 --> 01:09:14,317
Where is she?

679
01:09:14,422 --> 01:09:17,858
[Laughing]
Oh, this just gets better and better.

680
01:09:17,959 --> 01:09:19,688
Put it down.

681
01:09:21,562 --> 01:09:24,190
All right.

682
01:09:26,400 --> 01:09:29,597
<i>Easy, big guy.</i>
<i>He's still got something I need.</i>

683
01:09:29,704 --> 01:09:32,798
Listen, I don't care what you do with him.
I just want my wife.

684
01:09:32,907 --> 01:09:35,637
Oh, he's not gonna do
anything to me-

685
01:09:35,743 --> 01:09:39,201
Not until he finds out what happened
to those stolen diamonds.

686
01:09:39,313 --> 01:09:41,304
<i>'Cause that's what he's after-</i>

687
01:09:41,415 --> 01:09:43,610
His cut.

688
01:09:44,719 --> 01:09:47,779
Isn't that right, Officer?

689
01:09:47,889 --> 01:09:51,188
Now, why don't you
just take a second...

690
01:09:51,292 --> 01:09:53,658
and let that sink in there, champ?

691
01:09:57,465 --> 01:10:01,799
- Where are they, Rome?
- Where's what?

692
01:10:01,903 --> 01:10:03,837
Gimme my damn diamonds!

693
01:10:03,938 --> 01:10:05,997
Whoa! Calm down, V.B.

694
01:10:06,107 --> 01:10:08,302
I know our last deal
didn't work out too well...

695
01:10:08,409 --> 01:10:10,707
<i>but I'm willing to make a new one.</i>

696
01:10:10,811 --> 01:10:14,076
You see, I tried to kill this guy twice today.

697
01:10:14,182 --> 01:10:16,207
<i>He just won't die.</i>

698
01:10:17,318 --> 01:10:19,411
Maybe I'm having an off day.
I don't know.

699
01:10:19,520 --> 01:10:22,717
But if you shoot him right now...

700
01:10:23,991 --> 01:10:27,017
I'm willing to split
the diamonds with you.

701
01:10:27,128 --> 01:10:29,688
What do you say?

702
01:10:55,353 --> 01:10:58,117
- There's our ride. Let's go.
- Go where? What happened?

703
01:10:58,223 --> 01:11:00,191
A marine showed up, that's what.

704
01:11:00,291 --> 01:11:02,191
- John!
- He's still alive?

705
01:11:32,390 --> 01:11:34,483
[Groans]

706
01:11:38,730 --> 01:11:41,324
<i>[Rome]</i>
<i>Let's go!</i>

707
01:11:48,373 --> 01:11:50,933
Oh, no. You're not putting me in there.

708
01:11:51,042 --> 01:11:53,306
You're not putting me in there.

709
01:12:01,119 --> 01:12:03,053
<i>[Car Starts]</i>

710
01:12:14,465 --> 01:12:17,298
<i>[Siren Blaring]</i>

711
01:12:19,604 --> 01:12:23,062
Out of the water!
Get out of the water now!

712
01:12:32,483 --> 01:12:35,509
Turn around.
Put your hands above your head.

713
01:12:43,995 --> 01:12:46,725
Turn around.

714
01:12:46,831 --> 01:12:49,459
- I'm John Triton.
- Shut up!

715
01:12:49,567 --> 01:12:53,025
Down on your knees.
Lace your hands behind your head.

716
01:12:53,137 --> 01:12:56,004
- I'm the guy that called you. They have my wife.
- <i>Shut up, boy!</i>

717
01:12:56,107 --> 01:13:00,134
You're under arrest.
You have the right to remain silent.

718
01:13:00,244 --> 01:13:02,678
I suggest you use it.

719
01:13:05,016 --> 01:13:08,213
[Sharp Groan]
You're dead, boy!

720
01:13:19,530 --> 01:13:21,930
Look at that.

721
01:13:22,033 --> 01:13:24,024
You don't mind if I keep this one, do you?

722
01:13:28,272 --> 01:13:30,570
I'm sure we can work something out.

723
01:13:30,675 --> 01:13:33,576
- Work something out?
- [Chuckles]

724
01:13:40,485 --> 01:13:43,181
[Chuckles]
Whoa. Wait a minute, baby.

725
